    "body": "I am attempting this as a first issue.\r\n\r\nI traced the `is_scalar` function back to its [implementation which is in Cython](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/e56794984f17d1651d74e6dbcdbf77fbec53d45f/pandas/_libs/lib.pyx#L101) and it uses checks imported from the CPython datetime library to check the for the listed datetime objects. DateOffset objects are specific to Pandas so what would my next steps be here? I imagine importing DateOffset from where ever it's defined and using `isinstance` is not the answer..."
